<p><a name="Cultural_references" id="Cultural_references"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Golda_Meir&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: Cultural references">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Cultural references</span></h2>
<p>In Israel, the term "Golda's shoes" (<i>na'alei Golda</i>), a reference to the sturdy orthopedic shoes that Golda favored, has become a euphemism for all that is ugly and old-fashioned.<sup id="cite_ref-33" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-33" title=""><span>[</span>34<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><a name="Published_works" id="Published_works"></a></p>
